  "body": "## User Story\r\nAs a user, I want to see a consistent timestamp on chats between my devices.\r\n\r\n## Description\r\nChat timestamps have different formats on mobile and desktop.\r\n\r\n## Expected behavior\r\nSame date/time format for any device.\r\n\r\n## Actual behavior\r\n![img_7484](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/48645314-16ca0400-e9c4-11e8-8071-61a05cc5f1c0.PNG)\r\n<img width=\"341\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-11-16 a la s 5 18 20 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/48645319-19c4f480-e9c4-11e8-9159-eab58cbf3a07.png\">\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n### Today’s time\r\nFor messages within the current day, use uppercase AM or PM, without periods. Format **HH:MM AM/PM**\r\nExamples:\r\n* 02:00 AM\r\n* 10:30 PM\r\n\r\n### This week\r\nWithin the current week, use the day of the week until last Sunday. If the last message was yesterday, we show “**Yesterday**”.\r\nExamples:\r\n* Yesterday\r\n* Wednesday\r\n* Monday\r\n* Sunday\r\n\r\n### Any other date, this year\r\nWhen last message was before this week, and it’s within the current calendar year, we show the date without periods. Format **DD ShortMonth**\r\nShortMonth: Jan, Feb, Mar, Apr, May, Jun, Jul, Aug, Sep, Oct, Nov, Dec.\r\nExamples:\r\n* 16 Jan \r\n* 01 Feb \r\n\r\n### Any other date, before this year\r\nWhen last message was before the current calendar year, we show the date with the following format without periods **DD ShortMonth YYYY**\r\nExamples:\r\n* 16 Jan 2017\r\n* 01 Feb 2016\r\n\r\nExamples:\r\n![chat list - dates format - prposal 3 - winner _](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/48645455-83dd9980-e9c4-11e8-9357-9efeb84133de.png)\r\n![home tab](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/48645459-863ff380-e9c4-11e8-9232-c22edfa75df7.png)\r\n\r\n[Designs in Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/MRYBI5axcTwL4Ft8xAYhFOfy/Desktop-Chat?node-id=297%3A469)",
